\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {1}{\ignorespaces \textbf  {Method overview.} \textbf  {(a)} \emph  {ITB construction}: four dermoscopy datasets are programmatically degraded across five quality dimensions, scored by a 5-head IQA module to produce a per-image $\bar  q \in [0,1]$, and partitioned into the LQ/Edge/HQ/Diverse subsets used for evaluation. \textbf  {(b)} \emph  {QCTS}: on a frozen backbone, the logits $z$ are rescaled by a quality-conditioned temperature $T(\bar  q) = \mathrm  {softplus}(T_0 + \alpha (1{-}\bar  q))$; the two parameters $T_0, \alpha $ are fit by L-BFGS on the validation set, and $\alpha \!=\!0$ recovers standard temperature scaling. \emph  {Takeaway:} ITB and QCTS share a single per-image $\bar  q$, so adapting the framework to a new modality reduces to swapping the IQA module.}}{2}{figure.caption.1}\protected@file@percent }
\providecommand*\caption@xref[2]{\@setref\relax\@undefined{#1}}
\newlabel{fig:method}{{1}{2}{\textbf {Method overview.} \textbf {(a)} \emph {ITB construction}: four dermoscopy datasets are programmatically degraded across five quality dimensions, scored by a 5-head IQA module to produce a per-image $\bar q \in [0,1]$, and partitioned into the LQ/Edge/HQ/Diverse subsets used for evaluation. \textbf {(b)} \emph {QCTS}: on a frozen backbone, the logits $z$ are rescaled by a quality-conditioned temperature $T(\bar q) = \mathrm {softplus}(T_0 + \alpha (1{-}\bar q))$; the two parameters $T_0, \alpha $ are fit by L-BFGS on the validation set, and $\alpha \!=\!0$ recovers standard temperature scaling. \emph {Takeaway:} ITB and QCTS share a single per-image $\bar q$, so adapting the framework to a new modality reduces to swapping the IQA module}{figure.caption.1}{}}
